‘Wahala’ musician Portable has warned blogs to cease from spreading false narratives about him. Few days ago, the Police in Ogun State asked singer Portable to report for questioning over inciting violence or risk being arrested after being seen in a viral video asking his hangers-on to mercilessly beat up his former associate DJ Chicken. The musician, in the video, placed a hand on the shoulders of his estranged associate and accused him of sending a message to his wife advising her to send boys around Portable away.   How to play social media game, by Blessing CEO     Osimhen: Right person will leave you if…     ‘Buga’ is a mega hit, says Davido   Insisting he isn’t ‘wanted’ by the authorities, the “Zazu” crooner warned bloggers, particularly echoing the name of one, to stop spreading fake news about him. One post held the caption: “On my way back from IG Zone 2 Police office ZAZU Federal Government Liability… stop spreading fake news nothing like ZAZU is wanted.” Stressing on the matter, the father of two who recently married his babymama on the occasion of his second child’s christening added: “Stop spreading fake news about me Enough is enough. To those blogger carrying my fake news please be warned.”